THE Assistant Coach of the Tanga-based Coastal Union, Shaban Bakari said their team is gearing up to emerge victors in today’s Premier League match against Geita Gold at Nyankumbu School ground in Geita. Speaking during his team’s training at Nyamagana Stadium on Thursday, Bakari said they are ready for the match. “Our team has arrived in Mwanza safely and we have been able to train here at Nyamagana Stadium and the team is ready for the game. Our target is to win the game,” Bakari said. Bakari said his team will miss the services of their three players who are injured and they have remained in Tanga. He named the players as skipper Mtenje Albano, goalkeeper Mussa Mbisa and striker Gustavo Simon. , Coastal Union’s goalie Mohamed Hussein ‘Colour’ said they are determined to fight for the victory in all 90 minutes of the game. He called upon the team’s fans to come out in large numbers to support their team. In the ongoing Premier League standings, Coastal Union are placed ninth with 17 points after playing 14 matches. Coastal Union, the former Premier League champions, have won four, drawn five and lost five matches. They have scored 13 goals and conceded 10. Coastal Union lost their last three matches; 2-1 to Kagera Sugar at Kaitaba stadium in Kagera region. They also lost 2-0 to Young Africans and 3-1 to Namungo, both matches were played at Mkwakwani in Tanga.